Thank you Julie, for the kindness in your words to remind me that you think
I am begging and should take it private email. I see you have a box so your
tolerance of course is not quite like the others. I only wanted one simply
to communicate with friends and family and myself spiritually and nothing
else. Like taking it on the road. That I have no desire what&#39;s so ever. I
wanted one for strictly personal use. But, I am a smart lady and will build
my own and share I get with Frank privately. 

Please, be more considerate on this board. I shall not ask again. J Thanks
so much again for your reply,

Laura



From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
juli velazquez
Sent: Saturday, February 02, 2008 10:35 PM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Yeah--it works.



With all due respect, the man just got back on the board.  I don&#39;t think
that the very first thing he would like to get thrown at him is OH PLEASE
BUILD ME A BOX.  For if I had a pennie for every person in the last 2 years
I seen big to boxes and hit and run not sharing any of their data, I will be
a millionaire!!!



At least do it in private email.



Juli

Robin Searcy Henson &lt;MudPuddleFarm@...&gt; wrote:

Laura deserves a box Frank!!



Robin





----- Original Message ----- 

From: Laura &lt;mailto:gjk1rrfan@...&gt;  Kimberley 

To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com 

Sent: Saturday, February 02, 2008 7:55 PM

Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Yeah--it works.



Welcome back Frank,

I have a que stion for you. You have given boxes all men here in the group
except one man has any woman been given the opportunity to have a box? I
have requested one for a  long time now and even offered to pay you.

But if you just send me the schematics I will build it, I am studying
electronics now and here in Mexico the random would be a good thing I
believe. Because even though  there&#39;s no English speaking stations near me
all I get is English J

Laura

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Frank Sumption
Sent: Saturday, February 02, 2008 9:17 PM
To: evp-itc@yahoogroups.com
Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Yeah--it works.


 There is a lack of the background hiss, and white noise of the random tuned
systems.

 The sweep circuit is simple, and using pre-made tuners a real time saver,
provided a source for the older tuners can be found. I used to get them from
junk yards, but the old radios are getting harder to find. They have the
advantage of all the RF components matching the chip.

